02:03.757 --> 02:05.423
♪ Have yourself... ♪

02:05.425 --> 02:09.193
STEFAN: <i>Dear Elena,
This might be my last entry.</i>

02:09.196 --> 02:12.263
<i>There may be no tomorrow.</i>

02:12.265 --> 02:13.709
♪ Next year all our troubles... ♪

02:13.734 --> 02:15.170
<i>So, the present I'm giving myself</i>

02:15.195 --> 02:17.062
<i>this Christmas is...</i>

02:17.571 --> 02:19.737
<i>the present... today.</i>

02:19.739 --> 02:22.173
♪ Have yourself a
merry little Christmas... ♪

02:22.175 --> 02:23.942
<i>To get the twins back, I made a deal</i>

02:23.944 --> 02:26.211
<i>with the devil.</i>

02:26.213 --> 02:27.912
♪ Make the yuletide gay... ♪

02:27.914 --> 02:30.477
<i>At midnight, I have
to leave my life behind.</i>

02:30.502 --> 02:33.451
<i>Even though I just pledged
it to Caroline forever.</i>

02:35.689 --> 02:38.389
<i>If I can't find a way out of this,</i>

02:38.391 --> 02:40.825
<i>please remind her...</i>

02:40.827 --> 02:42.627
<i>I tried.</i>

02:42.629 --> 02:46.097
<i>I did everything I could
to get back to her.</i>

02:51.100 --> 02:54.101
I thought we agreed to cancel.

02:54.126 --> 02:55.118
Yeah, but you've been planning

02:55.142 --> 02:56.574
this Christmas Eve dinner forever,

02:56.576 --> 02:59.043
so we... are going to do it.

02:59.045 --> 03:00.111
Well, it's not about

03:00.113 --> 03:02.981
my plans, it's about... us

03:02.983 --> 03:05.116
and your deal with Cade.

03:05.118 --> 03:08.019
I think our last day of
life as we know it should be

03:08.021 --> 03:11.422
a little bit less depressing
than that, don't you?

03:11.424 --> 03:14.259
So, today, we are gonna do

03:14.261 --> 03:16.594
what people do on Christmas.

03:16.596 --> 03:18.129
We're gonna eat more than we should

03:18.131 --> 03:19.564
and we're gonna drink

03:19.566 --> 03:20.832
until our friends and family

03:20.834 --> 03:22.367
seem somewhat normal.

03:22.369 --> 03:24.602
(laughs)

03:27.540 --> 03:30.041
That's what I want today to be.

03:31.344 --> 03:33.945
(knocking)

03:34.673 --> 03:36.714
(gasps) Hi, girls.

03:36.716 --> 03:38.483
Merry Christmas, Mommy!

03:38.485 --> 03:40.151
Oh! Merry Christmas.

03:40.153 --> 03:41.286
Merry Christmas.

03:41.288 --> 03:44.289
Oh! Let me help take your jackets off.

03:44.291 --> 03:46.090
I'm afraid we're not gonna
be able to stay very long.

03:46.092 --> 03:47.458
What? Why?

03:47.460 --> 03:49.527
This is my last day with them for awhile.

03:49.529 --> 03:52.130
Yeah, well, uh,

03:52.132 --> 03:54.832
I take it you haven't spoken with Matt.

03:54.834 --> 03:55.833
No.

03:55.835 --> 03:57.502
Is Seline coming to dinner?

03:59.472 --> 04:00.738
No, honey.

04:00.740 --> 04:01.940
STEFAN: Hey.

04:01.942 --> 04:03.908
I thought I heard you two.

04:03.910 --> 04:05.310
I have your Christmas present

04:05.312 --> 04:06.744
upstairs.

04:06.746 --> 04:08.479
(cheering)

04:11.651 --> 04:13.051
(sighs)

04:13.053 --> 04:14.539
They're asking for Seline?

04:14.564 --> 04:15.653
I know.

04:15.655 --> 04:17.454
She kidnapped them.

04:17.457 --> 04:19.057
I guess they didn't register the danger.

04:19.059 --> 04:20.325
No, they just keep

04:20.350 --> 04:21.993
asking for her ever
since I got them back.

04:22.017 --> 04:24.262
Well, I don't want them
thinking that she's safe.

04:24.264 --> 04:25.863
I mean, who knows when
she's just gonna show up.

04:25.865 --> 04:27.031
I, uh...

04:27.033 --> 04:27.846
I'll talk to them.

04:27.871 --> 04:30.049
No, I'll talk to them... once we leave.

04:30.074 --> 04:32.403
But we're supposed to have
Christmas together first.

04:32.405 --> 04:33.571
What is it?

04:33.573 --> 04:34.539
Did something

04:34.541 --> 04:35.740
else happen?

04:35.742 --> 04:38.276
Look, I think you'll need
to sit down for this.

04:38.278 --> 04:40.078
Ho, ho,

04:40.080 --> 04:41.546
ho!

04:41.548 --> 04:43.481
Merry Christmas, Ric.

04:43.483 --> 04:44.515
I killed you.

04:44.517 --> 04:46.417
You what?!

04:46.419 --> 04:47.552
He deserved it.

04:47.554 --> 04:48.519
Yeah, he and Matt

04:48.521 --> 04:49.954
took a whack at me.

04:49.956 --> 04:51.456
They even buried me.

04:51.458 --> 04:53.558
I can't tell you how hard it was

04:53.560 --> 04:55.193
to get all of that dirt out.

04:55.195 --> 04:57.028
(chuckles) I know.

04:57.030 --> 04:58.296
I know.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.164
Christmas just got merry.

05:01.801 --> 05:04.068
Ah, I love it.

05:04.070 --> 05:05.269
I can totally use this

05:05.271 --> 05:07.114
to keep all my papers
from blowing away.

05:07.139 --> 05:08.205
(chuckles)

05:08.230 --> 05:09.574
I'm taking you to Paris,

05:09.576 --> 05:11.109
silly witch.

05:11.111 --> 05:12.510
(squeals)

05:12.512 --> 05:14.979
(both laugh)

05:14.981 --> 05:17.782
Say the word and we're off.

05:24.357 --> 05:26.891
(cell phone ringing)

05:28.928 --> 05:31.796
(laughs)

05:31.798 --> 05:33.598
I'm sorry.

05:33.600 --> 05:35.040
I know we're late.

05:35.065 --> 05:37.068
Thank goodness. Don't come.

05:37.070 --> 05:38.669
It's Damon. He's here with that

05:38.671 --> 05:40.805
psycho <i>American Idol</i> reject.

05:40.807 --> 05:42.740
Enzo cannot be around her.

05:42.742 --> 05:43.790
And don't even get me started

05:43.814 --> 05:45.877
on what Matt and Ric just tried to pull.

05:45.879 --> 05:47.912
What do Sybil and Damon want?

05:47.914 --> 05:50.108
To ruin Christmas, I don't know.

05:50.133 --> 05:51.015
(sighs)

05:51.017 --> 05:52.450
But they promised to leave my kids alone

05:52.452 --> 05:54.419
and I don't want a war.

05:54.421 --> 05:56.087
I just hope that they leave soon.

05:56.089 --> 05:57.655
ENZO: Well, what about the tuning fork?

05:57.657 --> 05:58.677
She stole it from us.

05:58.702 --> 05:59.991
Yeah, well, let's steal it back.

05:59.993 --> 06:01.092
From where? For all we know

06:01.094 --> 06:02.126
it's in the trunk of her car.

06:02.128 --> 06:03.294
It disrupts her psychic power

06:03.296 --> 06:04.529
and it hurts like hell.

06:04.531 --> 06:06.898
She won't be carrying it around with her.

06:06.900 --> 06:08.766
It's probably stashed
where she's staying.

06:08.768 --> 06:10.001
We have no idea where that is.

06:10.003 --> 06:11.280
I can try to find out.

06:11.305 --> 06:12.937
She's not gonna just tell you.

06:12.939 --> 06:14.072
She might.

06:14.074 --> 06:15.907
Let me call you back.

