contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:24.117 --> 06:27.785
♪ We wish you a merry Christmas ♪

06:27.787 --> 06:30.121
Eggnog?

06:30.123 --> 06:31.289
♪ We wish you... ♪

06:31.291 --> 06:33.524
I didn't have time to poison it.

06:33.526 --> 06:35.526
Well, you already poisoned the bourbon

06:35.528 --> 06:37.528
with milk and cinnamon, so...

06:37.530 --> 06:39.497
Ric's gonna stay with
the girls for awhile.

06:39.499 --> 06:40.731
DAMON: You don't have to hide them.

06:40.733 --> 06:42.300
I'm honoring the deal.

06:42.302 --> 06:44.102
We work for Cade.

06:44.104 --> 06:45.436
Munchkins go unharmed.

06:45.438 --> 06:46.637
Well, Ric's not

06:46.639 --> 06:48.506
exactly in a trusting mood right now

06:48.508 --> 06:49.640
and, uh...

06:49.642 --> 06:51.209
neither am I.

06:51.211 --> 06:52.677
SYBIL: My sister kidnapped them.

06:52.679 --> 06:54.979
I saved them from a life of serving Cade

06:54.981 --> 06:56.714
when I cosigned Damon's plan.

06:56.716 --> 06:59.717
So, put away your umbrella, Stefan.

06:59.719 --> 07:01.352
I don't need your shade.

07:01.354 --> 07:03.554
A simple thank you will suffice.

07:03.556 --> 07:05.056
Thank you.

07:06.069 --> 07:07.902
She's right.

07:07.927 --> 07:09.127
You can't fault one sibling

07:09.129 --> 07:11.229
for the sins of the other.

07:11.231 --> 07:12.296
Right?

07:12.298 --> 07:14.732
- I appreciate that.
- Stefan,

07:14.734 --> 07:16.100
why don't you come
with me and we'll go get

07:16.102 --> 07:18.503
some of the old family
tree ornaments, huh?

07:18.505 --> 07:21.372
Oh, come on, Stef.

07:23.109 --> 07:25.076
I'll tell you why I'm here.

07:25.912 --> 07:28.813
(Damon sighs)

07:30.083 --> 07:32.316
Mm.

07:34.320 --> 07:37.021
My murder, Stefan. They actually

07:37.023 --> 07:38.322
buried me in a shallow grave,

07:38.324 --> 07:39.997
not even in the family plot.

07:40.022 --> 07:42.059
Well, it's a little hard to be
sympathetic about your death

07:42.061 --> 07:43.394
when you're standing
right in front of me.

07:43.396 --> 07:46.597
Thanks to our eternal
agreement with Cade.

07:46.599 --> 07:48.533
What are you doing here?

07:48.535 --> 07:50.868
I'm getting ornaments
for the tree, Stefan.

07:50.870 --> 07:54.372
At midnight, I'm all
yours, so until then,

07:54.374 --> 07:57.041
would you just leave me alone, okay?

07:57.911 --> 07:59.877
You know, Saltzman going all

07:59.879 --> 08:03.247
crazy on me did have
an unexpected benefit.

08:03.249 --> 08:04.348
What's that?

08:04.350 --> 08:06.517
I got to hang out with
the new head honcho.

08:06.519 --> 08:07.518
Cade?

08:07.520 --> 08:09.854
The one and only.

08:10.790 --> 08:13.157
He's an interesting guy.

08:13.159 --> 08:14.525
You want time with him?

08:15.395 --> 08:18.129
Not particularly, no.

08:18.131 --> 08:21.832
Funny thing...

08:23.232 --> 08:25.046
(grunts)

08:25.071 --> 08:27.238
...he said the opposite about you.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.654
(gasps)

08:53.843 --> 08:55.977
(groans)

09:12.896 --> 09:14.295
Caroline?

09:15.231 --> 09:17.598
Mr. Salvatore.

09:17.600 --> 09:19.233
I've been waiting for you.

09:19.235 --> 09:21.335
Cade.

09:21.337 --> 09:23.671
Where are we?

09:24.607 --> 09:26.474
Just...

09:26.476 --> 09:29.076
behind the veil.

09:29.078 --> 09:30.812
So, this is hell?

09:30.814 --> 09:32.146
My living room?

09:32.148 --> 09:34.015
If this were hell,

09:34.017 --> 09:36.117
you would know it.

09:36.119 --> 09:38.352
Think of this as

09:38.354 --> 09:39.921
a waiting room.

09:39.923 --> 09:41.322
Lucky for you,

09:41.324 --> 09:43.057
I'm sending you back.

09:43.059 --> 09:46.727
But not before we
discuss our partnership.

09:46.729 --> 09:48.830
What's there to discuss?

09:48.832 --> 09:51.699
My brother and I fetch bad guys
for the rest of our existence

09:51.701 --> 09:52.800
and in exchange,

09:52.802 --> 09:54.135
you keep us out of hell.

09:54.137 --> 09:56.537
Seems pretty horrifically straightforward

09:56.539 --> 09:58.172
if you ask me.

09:58.174 --> 10:01.576
Surely, you must have questions.

10:01.578 --> 10:04.178
Just a Hail Mary pass since we're here.

10:04.180 --> 10:06.214
Why don't you let me out of this deal?

10:06.216 --> 10:08.015
I'm not the right person for you.

10:08.017 --> 10:09.650
Actually...

10:09.652 --> 10:12.019
you're the perfect person.

10:12.021 --> 10:13.488
I'm here

10:13.490 --> 10:14.856
to show you why.

10:16.125 --> 10:19.994
Mmm, this is gonna be a killer dinner.

10:19.996 --> 10:21.729
Are the other guests on the way?

10:21.731 --> 10:23.197
Let's hope so.

10:23.199 --> 10:24.432
Goody.

10:24.434 --> 10:26.100
I can't wait.

10:26.102 --> 10:30.505
I haven't had a Christmas
Eve dinner in... ever.

10:30.507 --> 10:33.307
(sighs)

10:33.309 --> 10:35.843
Here, here, here.

10:35.845 --> 10:38.045
- Let me help.
- (laughs)

10:39.626 --> 10:40.992
Besides,

10:41.017 --> 10:42.483
you wouldn't want to get

10:42.485 --> 10:44.252
turkey juice on that gigantic rock

10:44.254 --> 10:46.754
on your finger.

10:47.824 --> 10:48.856
So?

10:48.858 --> 10:50.591
When's the wedding?

10:50.593 --> 10:53.361
It was supposed to be in June,

10:53.363 --> 10:55.496
- but...
- Oh, that's right.

10:55.498 --> 10:57.298
Cade. Hmm.

10:57.300 --> 10:59.700
Don't worry. A vampire like Stefan

10:59.702 --> 11:01.168
will be really good.

11:01.170 --> 11:03.371
He can probably kill 12 people

11:03.373 --> 11:04.572
in two seconds...

11:04.574 --> 11:06.774
(gulps)

11:06.776 --> 11:09.377
...and still be home in
time to draw you a bath.

11:09.379 --> 11:11.579
Thrilling.

11:11.581 --> 11:15.449
So, what's your favorite part
about Mystic Falls so far?

11:15.451 --> 11:17.218
Hmm...

11:17.220 --> 11:19.720
Huge houses with big pools.

11:19.722 --> 11:21.522
You know I love the water,

11:21.524 --> 11:23.991
and it's not like I have to
pay the mortgage or anything.

11:23.993 --> 11:27.194
It's hard to find those around here.

11:27.196 --> 11:28.729
Actually, there's a little neighborhood

11:28.731 --> 11:30.097
outside of Grove Hill

11:30.099 --> 11:32.800
called the Pond Estates.

11:33.356 --> 11:34.922
Weirdly though,

11:34.947 --> 11:36.437
there's no pond.

11:36.439 --> 11:39.073
(laughs) I know, right?

11:39.075 --> 11:43.077
Anyway, it's filled with rich, sleazy men

11:43.079 --> 11:46.447
that'll give up their
whole house for a song.

11:46.449 --> 11:47.682
Get it?

11:47.684 --> 11:48.816
(laughs)

11:48.818 --> 11:50.885
That's hilarious.

11:50.887 --> 11:52.820
Hmm.

11:52.822 --> 11:55.323
I'll be right back.

11:57.994 --> 11:59.961
(sighs)

11:59.963 --> 12:01.662
There's a McMansion neighborhood called

12:01.664 --> 12:03.464
the Pond Estates.

12:03.466 --> 12:04.899
It's somewhere outside of Grove Hill.

12:04.901 --> 12:06.000
Okay. We'll look it up.

12:06.002 --> 12:07.234
Are you guys okay?

12:07.236 --> 12:09.136
It is insane around here.

12:09.138 --> 12:11.305
Sybil wants to be my bestie.

12:11.307 --> 12:14.308
Lizzie and Josie keep
asking about Seline.

12:14.310 --> 12:16.744
And I'm pretty sure Stefan's
just off hiding somewhere.

12:16.746 --> 12:19.146
It's times like these
I really miss Elena.

12:19.148 --> 12:21.349
If she were here, Damon
wouldn't be doing any of this.

12:21.351 --> 12:22.984
Yeah, well, she's not here,

12:22.986 --> 12:24.151
and...

12:24.153 --> 12:26.187
BONNIE: Caroline?

12:26.189 --> 12:28.189
Caroline.

12:28.191 --> 12:29.757
I need another gift box.

12:29.759 --> 12:31.659
(beeps)

12:31.661 --> 12:33.127
♪ ♪

12:33.129 --> 12:35.463
Stefan?

12:37.300 --> 12:38.966
Stefan! Stefan...

12:38.968 --> 12:40.968
(gasps)

12:44.507 --> 12:46.073
(exhales)

12:46.075 --> 12:48.843
DAMON: Relax. He's not dead.

12:48.845 --> 12:50.711
Have you seen Ric?

12:50.713 --> 12:53.481
Because if that's what's
holding up dinner...

12:54.984 --> 12:56.684
(grunts)

12:56.686 --> 12:58.219
What did you do?

12:58.221 --> 13:02.289
I killed him. I mean,
technically, he is dead.

13:02.291 --> 13:03.824
But he'll be back.

13:03.826 --> 13:05.393
Your baby daddy staked me

13:05.395 --> 13:07.194
and I don't have a scratch.

13:07.196 --> 13:08.529
Same dealio.

13:08.531 --> 13:11.298
(panting)

13:11.300 --> 13:14.835
Big man requested a meeting.

13:14.837 --> 13:17.972
What was I gonna do?

13:17.974 --> 13:20.041
You know...

13:20.043 --> 13:21.475
I bet...

13:21.477 --> 13:24.707
that if you just wash this off...

13:26.849 --> 13:28.783
...it might still work.

13:28.785 --> 13:30.918
♪ ♪

13:40.196 --> 13:42.596
(exhales)

13:42.598 --> 13:45.499
"But I heard him exclaim,
'ere he drove out of sight,

13:45.501 --> 13:47.968
"Merry Christmas to all,

13:47.970 --> 13:50.304
and to all a good-night."

13:50.306 --> 13:53.040
One more story, Daddy.

13:53.042 --> 13:55.943
(chuckles) Okay. One more,
but then a nap,

13:55.945 --> 13:58.779
because Santa Claus is
scheduled to drop by

13:58.781 --> 14:00.114
any minute now.

14:00.116 --> 14:01.582
LIZZIE: Uncle Stefan says

14:01.584 --> 14:03.818
our palace is the safest place

14:03.820 --> 14:04.952
in the whole world.

14:04.954 --> 14:06.454
And Uncle Stefan's right.

14:06.456 --> 14:09.457
But remember. Never
open the palace doors

14:09.459 --> 14:12.584
for anyone but Mommy,
Daddy and Uncle Stefan, okay?

14:12.609 --> 14:13.961
LIZZIE: And Seline.

14:13.963 --> 14:16.097
(lullaby music playing)

14:18.401 --> 14:22.103
♪ On the first day of Christmas
my true love sent to me ♪

14:22.105 --> 14:24.772
♪ A partridge in a pear tree... ♪

14:24.774 --> 14:27.208
Do you like these ornaments?

14:27.210 --> 14:29.877
Nope. Not even a little bit.

14:29.879 --> 14:32.847
Hey. Surprise, surprise.

14:32.849 --> 14:35.793
Matt! I thought you said
that you weren't coming.

14:35.818 --> 14:38.152
Uh. apparently, the Mystic Grill
wasn't good enough for this guy.

14:38.154 --> 14:40.488
Holidays are special. I convinced him

14:40.490 --> 14:42.323
he should stick around
for the people he loves.

14:42.325 --> 14:45.226
Which is a hell of a lot
more than he can say for you,

14:45.251 --> 14:46.690
Peter Maxwell.

14:46.715 --> 14:48.662
SYBIL: (gasps) Ooh!

14:48.664 --> 14:51.098
- We've been waiting for you.
- CAROLINE: Well,

14:51.100 --> 14:53.534
Damon's alive, as you can see.

14:53.536 --> 14:55.870
Bonnie and Enzo are late.
And Stefan's dead!

14:55.872 --> 14:58.405
Merry Christmas. I've got gifts.

14:59.442 --> 15:01.909
Where is this?

15:03.079 --> 15:04.979
I worked here.

15:04.981 --> 15:06.614
I picked grapes.

15:06.616 --> 15:08.349
Pomegranates, I think.

15:08.351 --> 15:10.851
Those aren't grapes.

15:10.853 --> 15:13.420
But it is your work.

15:16.692 --> 15:18.926
♪ ♪

15:20.029 --> 15:22.630
Ringing a bell?

15:23.933 --> 15:26.000
Take another look.

15:26.002 --> 15:29.271
If death is your canvas...

15:30.006 --> 15:34.108
...this is your masterpiece.

15:34.110 --> 15:37.044
Nothing but evil

15:37.046 --> 15:39.547
could produce this.

15:43.786 --> 15:46.453
I decided you were mine.

15:46.455 --> 15:49.056
Right here. Monterey.

15:50.326 --> 15:51.959
Christmas.

15:51.961 --> 15:53.327
1917.

15:53.329 --> 15:55.162
Christmas?

15:56.332 --> 15:58.199
I wasn't here on Christmas.

15:58.201 --> 16:00.201
On the contrary, Ripper.

16:03.706 --> 16:06.273
Look, I know what damage
I've to done to these people.

16:06.275 --> 16:09.643
I've been living with that
guilt for a hundred years.

16:09.645 --> 16:11.846
But not on Christmas.

16:11.848 --> 16:15.316
I wouldn't do that...

16:19.155 --> 16:23.157
Let's make sue we all get back
to the spirit of Christmas.

16:23.159 --> 16:25.860
At the heart of it is forgiveness.

16:25.862 --> 16:28.166
So, Matt.

16:28.731 --> 16:29.864
Peter.

16:29.866 --> 16:31.198
Thanks.

16:31.200 --> 16:33.067
And my mother

16:33.069 --> 16:36.470
taught me to always be prepared

16:36.472 --> 16:38.138
for anything.

16:38.140 --> 16:39.607
Thank you.

16:39.609 --> 16:41.008
♪ Don we now our gay apparel ♪

16:41.010 --> 16:42.509
♪ Fa-la-la, la-la-la... ♪

16:42.511 --> 16:44.745
Now, this one...

16:44.747 --> 16:46.714
is for Damon.

16:46.716 --> 16:48.616
Even though we've had our moments,

16:48.618 --> 16:51.418
I know that there is a future you

16:51.420 --> 16:55.155
that is going to ask for
my forgiveness one day.

16:56.726 --> 16:58.826
This is for that guy.

16:58.828 --> 17:01.362
♪ ♪

17:02.999 --> 17:05.266
DAMON: Anyway... (clears throat)

17:05.268 --> 17:07.667
I'm sure you're all asking yourselves why

17:07.670 --> 17:09.036
I barged in tonight.

17:09.038 --> 17:11.605
Relax. I come bearing a gift.

17:11.607 --> 17:13.307
Now, unfortunately,
I'm only gonna be able to give it

17:13.309 --> 17:16.143
to the most despicably
evil person in the room,

17:16.145 --> 17:17.877
and that's gonna be a tough decision.

17:17.880 --> 17:18.846
But tonight,

17:18.848 --> 17:20.180
one lucky little elf

17:20.182 --> 17:22.016
is gonna get an all expense paid,

17:22.018 --> 17:23.684
one-way trip,

17:23.685 --> 17:25.920
straight to hell.

17:25.922 --> 17:27.421
Meaning,

17:27.423 --> 17:29.957
I'm gonna kill one of you.

17:34.664 --> 17:36.163
Let's eat.

17:41.124 --> 17:42.724
Hey. You sure this is it?

17:42.726 --> 17:44.025
Four houses had pools.

17:44.027 --> 17:45.260
Only one had lights on.

17:45.262 --> 17:46.861
Call it intuition.

17:46.863 --> 17:48.129
Do the honors?

17:48.131 --> 17:50.498
(door opens)

17:53.737 --> 17:54.836
(door slams)

17:54.838 --> 17:56.171
(groans)

17:57.174 --> 17:58.340
(chuckles softly)

17:58.342 --> 18:00.742
She picked a place with an owner.

18:00.744 --> 18:02.711
I'll be fine.

18:02.713 --> 18:04.479
I can do it.

18:04.481 --> 18:06.514
All right.

18:08.194 --> 18:10.118
WOMAN: ♪ Deck the halls
with boughs of holly ♪

18:10.120 --> 18:12.287
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

18:12.289 --> 18:15.023
♪ 'Tis the season to be jolly,
fa-la-la-la-la ♪

18:15.025 --> 18:16.291
♪ La-la-la-la ♪

18:16.293 --> 18:18.493
♪ Don we now our gay apparel ♪

18:18.495 --> 18:20.295
- ♪ Fa-la-la, la-la-la, la-la-la. ♪
- I know you're here.

18:20.297 --> 18:21.696
Tammy,

18:21.698 --> 18:23.932
extend an invitation to our
other guest, please.

18:23.934 --> 18:25.066
His name is Enzo,

18:25.068 --> 18:27.035
and he's probably freezing.

18:27.037 --> 18:28.837
Enzo, do come in, young man.

18:28.839 --> 18:30.205
Enzo, no!

18:31.241 --> 18:33.408
I'm not gonna harm him. Or you.

18:33.410 --> 18:35.076
I'm not Sybil.

18:35.078 --> 18:36.745
Okay. We'll just leave, then.

18:36.747 --> 18:37.846
Without the weapon?

18:37.848 --> 18:39.080
That is what you came for.

18:39.082 --> 18:41.070
Sybil left for Mystic Falls.

18:41.095 --> 18:42.851
You two show up here.

18:42.853 --> 18:44.653
It doesn't take a psychic to know

18:44.655 --> 18:46.855
it's not to keep me company.

18:46.857 --> 18:49.491
Besides, that's what
I sirened Tammy's family for.

18:49.493 --> 18:52.560
Who wants to be alone on Christmas?

18:56.066 --> 18:58.133
Bring me your phone, Bonnie.

18:59.870 --> 19:01.836
It's really quite simple.

19:01.838 --> 19:05.006
I assess the evil in people,
so if they are wicked,

19:05.008 --> 19:07.041
immoral, corrupt,

19:07.043 --> 19:08.276
foul, nefarious,

19:08.278 --> 19:10.144
et cetera, I kill them.

19:11.214 --> 19:13.047
These are the au gratin potatoes.

19:13.049 --> 19:15.527
Stefan made them.
They're a Salvatore recipe.

19:15.552 --> 19:17.585
Hey, where the hell is Ric?
What was he, reading

19:17.587 --> 19:19.053
the dictionary to those girls?

19:19.055 --> 19:20.875
You are not going to kill Ric...

19:20.900 --> 19:22.657
or anybody else.

19:22.659 --> 19:24.592
We are just going to sit here

19:24.594 --> 19:26.327
and enjoy this nice dinner

19:26.329 --> 19:28.463
just like Stefan wanted.

19:30.967 --> 19:32.033
DAMON: What?

19:32.035 --> 19:34.102
Was just breaking some bread.

19:34.104 --> 19:36.304
Why are you doing this?

19:36.306 --> 19:39.374
- It's kind of his job.
- To murder innocent people?

19:39.376 --> 19:41.876
Look who's talking about murder.

19:43.013 --> 19:45.380
- I never killed...
- Oh, yeah?

19:45.382 --> 19:47.582
Your old flame Penny is
pretty dead as a door...

19:47.584 --> 19:49.484
(slams table) I never murdered anyone.

19:49.486 --> 19:51.519
CAROLINE: Matt.

19:51.521 --> 19:52.987
Please.

19:56.259 --> 19:57.992
DAMON: You know, at least Ric

19:57.994 --> 20:00.662
looked a little torn up when
that stake went in my heart.

20:00.664 --> 20:02.530
And you looked pretty psyched.

20:02.532 --> 20:04.699
But I forgive you, Mattie.

20:04.701 --> 20:07.101
You've had a lot of tragedy in your life.

20:08.138 --> 20:10.138
Here's the deal. Ric was just doing

20:10.140 --> 20:11.773
the parental thing, much like what

20:11.775 --> 20:13.608
he's doing upstairs right now.

20:13.610 --> 20:14.909
Do I want to kill him?

20:14.911 --> 20:16.695
Yes, but that's personal.

20:16.720 --> 20:18.913
This should be principle.

20:18.915 --> 20:20.982
It's all personal, Damon.

20:20.984 --> 20:22.650
SYBIL: What about this...

20:22.652 --> 20:24.419
Peter fellow?

20:25.555 --> 20:27.155
I've heard so so much about you.

20:27.157 --> 20:28.756
Back off.

20:28.758 --> 20:30.959
Or what?

20:30.961 --> 20:32.460
- Bonnie?
- SELINE: Don't hang up.

20:32.462 --> 20:34.429
Bonnie and Enzo are here with me.

20:34.431 --> 20:37.131
They're in no danger.

20:37.133 --> 20:39.400
We're fine, Ric. Seline
just wants to talk to you.

20:39.402 --> 20:42.003
She won't give us the weapon
unless we got you on the phone.

20:42.005 --> 20:43.605
What the hell do you have to say?

20:43.607 --> 20:44.906
Your children need my help.

20:44.908 --> 20:47.108
My children are just fine.

20:47.110 --> 20:49.112
And you're never gonna come
around them ever again.

20:49.137 --> 20:50.011
I have to.

20:50.013 --> 20:51.846
I need to fix what I started.

20:51.848 --> 20:53.481
I was giving them training,

20:53.483 --> 20:56.184
preparing them for Cade.
That left a psychic imprint.

20:56.186 --> 20:57.585
If I don't remove that imprint,

20:57.587 --> 21:00.121
they will always be linked to me.

21:00.123 --> 21:01.889
They must be showing signs of it by now.

21:01.891 --> 21:05.426
Look, I did what you asked,
and I got on the phone.

21:05.428 --> 21:06.527
Now it's your turn.

21:06.529 --> 21:08.630
Give my friends what they need.

21:08.632 --> 21:10.632
Alaric, I'm not who you think I am.

21:10.634 --> 21:12.967
I have been trying to escape for years.

21:12.969 --> 21:14.802
Then do us all a favor.

21:14.804 --> 21:16.571
And drop dead.

21:16.573 --> 21:18.373
(sighs)

21:19.142 --> 21:22.343
Something nice and easy, Tammy.

21:22.345 --> 21:26.571
♪ O holy night... ♪

21:26.596 --> 21:28.922
If that's your Christmas list,
then you better get cracking.

21:28.946 --> 21:31.686
Sadly, it's not that kind of list.

21:31.688 --> 21:33.354
Georgie Dowling?

21:33.356 --> 21:34.822
Ric's intern?

21:34.824 --> 21:37.091
She's the last person I killed.

21:38.228 --> 21:40.628
It's reverse chronological order.

21:40.630 --> 21:42.286
The names were

21:42.311 --> 21:43.931
a habit I picked up along the way.

21:43.933 --> 21:46.834
Where'd you pick that up, exactly?

21:48.872 --> 21:50.638
<i>In Monterey.</i>

21:50.640 --> 21:53.641
STEFAN: I don't remember doing this.

21:53.643 --> 21:55.843
Recognize him?

22:08.558 --> 22:12.026
CADE: That you showed
remorse meant nothing to me.

22:13.930 --> 22:16.264
But for some reason,

22:16.266 --> 22:17.932
it did to her.

22:37.034 --> 22:39.635
Does this jog your memory?

22:54.018 --> 22:57.653
Who are they? Your victims?

22:58.522 --> 22:59.855
Leave...

22:59.857 --> 23:01.768
or you'll go up there next.

23:01.793 --> 23:04.092
You are too exhausted to hurt me.

23:05.930 --> 23:10.265
(humming)

23:12.603 --> 23:14.803
You will rest now.

23:14.805 --> 23:17.472
In torment.

23:18.609 --> 23:21.410
My master has claimed your soul.

23:25.249 --> 23:26.882
(yelling)

23:26.884 --> 23:29.618
Stefan Salvatore?

23:29.620 --> 23:30.852
Are you sure?

23:30.854 --> 23:32.487
Positive.

23:32.489 --> 23:36.391
I had every intention of eating his flesh.

23:36.393 --> 23:38.360
I had ripped apart so many others

23:38.362 --> 23:39.695
but none of them massacred

23:39.697 --> 23:42.297
an entire work camp on Christmas Eve.

23:43.410 --> 23:45.334
Ironic, huh?

23:45.336 --> 23:46.835
What made you spare him?

23:46.837 --> 23:50.505
When I looked into his mind,

23:50.507 --> 23:52.975
I didn't see evil.

23:52.977 --> 23:55.944
I only saw anguish.

23:55.946 --> 23:57.112
(gasps)

23:58.515 --> 24:01.316
You can see inside my mind, can't you?

24:01.318 --> 24:03.051
It's horrible, isn't it?

24:03.053 --> 24:04.486
I know.

24:04.488 --> 24:05.787
Take me. I deserve it.

24:05.789 --> 24:07.022
Yes, you do.

24:07.024 --> 24:09.224
I was made into a Ripper who craves blood

24:09.226 --> 24:10.525
all day and all night.

24:10.527 --> 24:12.728
Kill me. Do it.

24:12.730 --> 24:14.830
Please.

24:16.000 --> 24:17.466
(sighs)

24:17.468 --> 24:19.801
(gasping)

24:19.803 --> 24:22.337
I saw a man who was innocent,

24:22.339 --> 24:24.439
had loved,

24:24.441 --> 24:27.042
and then had to become
a monster to survive.

24:29.179 --> 24:32.280
<i>That's a story I know all too well.</i>

24:32.883 --> 24:34.750
<i>Maybe he deserved Cade's wrath,</i>

24:34.752 --> 24:38.253
<i>but I no longer wanted
to be the one to decide.</i>

24:44.094 --> 24:46.128
She took the memory away.

24:46.130 --> 24:48.030
CADE: She altered your
subconscious enough

24:48.032 --> 24:49.765
that you forgot on your own.

24:49.767 --> 24:54.236
Made me believe I was worthy of a life.

24:54.238 --> 24:56.071
Yeah.

24:56.073 --> 24:58.273
Weak.

24:58.275 --> 25:00.475
I knew I had lost her.

25:00.477 --> 25:04.279
But it piqued my interest... in you.

25:05.115 --> 25:07.516
You're a savage killer

25:07.518 --> 25:10.419
who escaped fate and
turned my best servant

25:10.421 --> 25:11.987
into a mush of remorse.

25:11.989 --> 25:14.589
That combination

25:14.591 --> 25:16.691
makes you valuable.

25:16.693 --> 25:18.860
That's why I jumped at the opportunity

25:18.862 --> 25:21.563
to have you as my new servant.

25:21.565 --> 25:24.032
You...

25:24.034 --> 25:27.669
a coldhearted killing machine,

25:27.671 --> 25:29.371
instead of some reluctant girl

25:29.373 --> 25:31.606
who found morality a hundred years ago.

25:31.608 --> 25:33.275
I will never...

25:33.277 --> 25:34.509
be that Ripper again.

25:34.511 --> 25:37.112
Not for you.

25:37.114 --> 25:38.380
Not anyone.

25:38.382 --> 25:41.283
I'm disappointed to hear it.

25:41.285 --> 25:43.919
Hmm. That Ripper

25:43.921 --> 25:47.122
is exactly what I want in a servant.

25:50.060 --> 25:52.461
One more stop.

26:02.439 --> 26:04.439
All I wanted was a way out.

26:06.276 --> 26:08.143
I always wanted to be mortal.

26:09.279 --> 26:10.645
To be free.

26:11.748 --> 26:14.449
But now, when I die,

26:14.451 --> 26:16.785
Cade will torture my soul in hell.

26:18.589 --> 26:21.189
Because my sister sold me out.

26:23.293 --> 26:26.361
Redemption is the only chance I have.

26:28.632 --> 26:29.798
(tuning fork clinks)

26:32.369 --> 26:34.669
If Alaric loves his daughters,

26:35.639 --> 26:38.807
he will bring them to see me.

26:41.745 --> 26:43.778
We'll relay the message.

26:46.383 --> 26:48.116
Can't promise results.

26:49.553 --> 26:52.521
The path to forgiveness begins
with one step, right?

26:53.790 --> 26:56.124
Thank you.

26:58.095 --> 26:59.394
PETER: I told you.

26:59.396 --> 27:00.662
I gambled away lots of money.

27:00.664 --> 27:02.429
I cheated on my taxes for sure.

27:02.454 --> 27:04.633
I don't know what else you want to know.

27:04.635 --> 27:06.501
Well, look who decided to join us.

27:06.503 --> 27:07.636
I was just asking Peter what's

27:07.638 --> 27:09.404
the worst thing he's ever done.

27:09.406 --> 27:11.306
Oh, well, mine was not making sure you

27:11.308 --> 27:12.807
that you were permanently dead.

27:12.809 --> 27:15.477
I see you're wreaking havoc as usual.

27:15.479 --> 27:17.679
Damon, drop this stupid game.

27:17.681 --> 27:21.416
Oh, but humiliating public
confession is so fun.

27:21.418 --> 27:22.551
You left your son.

27:22.553 --> 27:24.052
You abandoned your family.

27:24.054 --> 27:26.588
And your answer to the question
what's the worst thing

27:26.590 --> 27:27.422
you've ever done is...

27:27.424 --> 27:28.356
(imitating Peter): "Uh,

27:28.358 --> 27:29.791
"I guess I gambled and cheated

27:29.793 --> 27:31.526
on account of my dishonesty."

27:31.528 --> 27:32.561
I was a kid.

27:32.563 --> 27:33.762
Well, unless your last name is Pan,

27:33.764 --> 27:35.964
you haven't been a kid for a long time.

27:35.966 --> 27:38.867
So, explain to me

27:38.869 --> 27:41.036
the last 20-plus years.

27:41.038 --> 27:42.571
None of your business, Damon.

27:43.646 --> 27:46.066
Enough! Enough.

27:46.091 --> 27:48.076
This has gone way too far.

27:48.078 --> 27:49.544
You do not need to answer him.

27:53.025 --> 27:54.893
Yes you do. And quick.

27:54.918 --> 27:56.451
(yells)

27:56.453 --> 27:58.520
Next cut goes a couple inches lower.

27:58.522 --> 27:59.875
What are you gonna do, Donovan?

27:59.900 --> 28:00.822
Kill me again?

28:00.824 --> 28:02.123
Let's hear Papa's story

28:02.125 --> 28:03.725
while he still has some vocal cords.

28:03.727 --> 28:05.660
Last chance.

28:05.662 --> 28:09.331
What kept you away
for more than 20 years?

28:09.333 --> 28:12.100
It was shame, okay? Just look, I was...

28:12.102 --> 28:13.868
I was ashamed.

28:13.870 --> 28:15.937
Kelly was pregnant again and I...

28:15.939 --> 28:18.240
I couldn't come back and
be another toilet scrubber

28:18.242 --> 28:20.775
in this town, I had...

28:20.777 --> 28:22.244
I had to get out.

28:22.246 --> 28:24.980
(breathing heavily)

28:24.982 --> 28:27.082
DAMON: Wow.

28:27.084 --> 28:28.917
It's worse than I thought.

28:28.919 --> 28:30.885
He didn't have a reason at all.

28:34.324 --> 28:36.324
Ladies and gentlemen,

28:37.329 --> 28:38.662
we have a winner.

28:45.758 --> 28:47.555
(school bell rings)

28:48.739 --> 28:50.205
Why are we here?

28:50.207 --> 28:53.842
CADE: This is moments
before you first met her,

28:53.844 --> 28:55.577
literally ran into her.

28:56.914 --> 28:58.380
Elena.

28:58.382 --> 29:01.103
If only you had never
come down this hallway,

29:01.128 --> 29:02.651
we might not be together now.

29:02.653 --> 29:03.785
This was from a chapter in my life

29:03.787 --> 29:05.220
when I was good.

29:05.222 --> 29:06.314
I loved her.

29:06.339 --> 29:08.624
She already had enough
tragedy in her life.

29:08.626 --> 29:10.959
You just had to insert yourself.

29:10.961 --> 29:13.695
All because you "had to know her."

29:13.697 --> 29:17.533
You took a good girl whose life
was headed down the right path

29:17.535 --> 29:20.936
and you veered her right into the median.

29:20.938 --> 29:23.639
That was never my intention.

29:23.641 --> 29:25.274
I tried to protect her.

29:25.276 --> 29:26.909
Never meeting her...

29:26.911 --> 29:28.343
was the only way to protect her.

29:28.345 --> 29:32.381
But instead, you chose a total stranger

29:32.383 --> 29:35.250
and turned her into something dark.

29:35.252 --> 29:38.087
(school bell rings)

29:39.990 --> 29:42.070
Well, I can't take that back, can I?

29:42.793 --> 29:45.727
But you can do it again.

29:45.729 --> 29:47.930
For me.

29:47.932 --> 29:49.665
Find people that would get into the place

29:49.667 --> 29:52.134
with pearly gates by an inch,

29:52.136 --> 29:55.270
and make them into folks
that would miss it by a mile.

29:55.272 --> 29:57.114
Like Elena.

29:57.139 --> 29:58.874
Help me gather what I need.

29:58.876 --> 30:00.809
But Elena is a good person.

30:00.811 --> 30:03.078
I thought you needed evil people.

30:03.080 --> 30:05.747
Good people who can be made wicked.

30:06.417 --> 30:08.150
They are evil

30:08.152 --> 30:10.586
at their core.

30:10.588 --> 30:12.554
Their souls are unusually potent.

30:13.872 --> 30:17.340
Those are the ones I want
to feed on most of all.

30:18.529 --> 30:21.163
I'm so sorry about your face.

30:21.165 --> 30:22.598
Me?

30:22.600 --> 30:26.235
I prefer to catch my flies with honey.

30:26.237 --> 30:27.669
See, Damon

30:27.671 --> 30:30.272
came here to give something,

30:30.274 --> 30:32.774
but I came here to get something.

30:32.776 --> 30:35.444
So, where is it?

30:36.347 --> 30:38.680
Whatever you want,
look, I-I don't have it.

30:38.682 --> 30:40.115
Lies.

30:40.117 --> 30:41.884
Lady, I have no idea

30:41.886 --> 30:43.185
what you're talking about.

30:43.187 --> 30:44.486
All you need to know

30:44.488 --> 30:46.255
is that you have something I need,

30:46.257 --> 30:47.923
and you will give it to me.

30:47.925 --> 30:50.592
(yelling)

30:50.594 --> 30:52.694
I wouldn't.

30:54.265 --> 30:56.165
(door opens, closes)

30:56.167 --> 30:57.967
(yelling)

30:57.992 --> 31:00.202
Simple mind, where is it?

31:00.204 --> 31:01.904
(Peter groaning)

31:01.906 --> 31:04.106
- (tuning fork ringing)
- (gasping)

31:05.376 --> 31:06.642
Are you all right, love?

31:06.644 --> 31:09.378
(groaning)

31:15.352 --> 31:17.452
You've taken too much of my time.

31:17.454 --> 31:18.854
I suppose.

31:18.856 --> 31:21.156
Especially considering
I have forever with you.

31:21.158 --> 31:22.891
And if I refuse?

31:23.894 --> 31:26.662
I suddenly become patient enough

31:26.664 --> 31:29.531
to wait for those kids upstairs

31:29.533 --> 31:31.333
to come of age.

31:36.106 --> 31:40.342
And what if you don't have to be patient?

31:40.344 --> 31:42.911
What if I can get the job done...

31:42.913 --> 31:44.613
faster?

31:45.749 --> 31:47.316
"Faster"?

31:48.686 --> 31:50.018
How?

31:50.020 --> 31:52.120
I could become the Ripper that you want.

31:52.122 --> 31:55.357
I'd be more effective that way.

31:55.359 --> 31:57.459
I wouldn't be held back by my emotions.

31:57.461 --> 31:59.228
You'd turn your humanity off?

31:59.230 --> 32:00.862
For a short time, yes.

32:00.864 --> 32:04.433
And then after, when it's over,

32:04.435 --> 32:06.435
you let me and my brother go.

32:09.039 --> 32:12.040
When I was the Ripper...

32:12.042 --> 32:14.710
I was one of a kind.

32:14.712 --> 32:19.047
No one can do what I do.

32:21.685 --> 32:23.252
One year.

32:24.955 --> 32:29.791
Although the beast I saw in Monterey

32:29.793 --> 32:32.227
will never tire of this work.

32:32.229 --> 32:35.631
I predict that, after a year with me,

32:35.633 --> 32:38.767
you won't want to leave.

32:40.571 --> 32:42.804
Well, I think you're wrong.

32:42.806 --> 32:47.276
That's what makes our wager worthwhile.

32:49.780 --> 32:52.981
CAROLERS: ♪ Silent night... ♪

32:52.983 --> 32:54.383
DAMON: How's your head?

32:54.385 --> 32:57.085
Aside from the wine, it's okay.

32:57.087 --> 32:58.420
Good.

32:58.422 --> 33:01.089
You saved me tonight.

33:01.091 --> 33:03.492
It was instinct.

33:05.162 --> 33:07.095
Something's happening...

33:07.097 --> 33:10.365
in there.

33:10.367 --> 33:13.435
I didn't know you had one of those.

33:13.437 --> 33:15.604
- Mm, must be the holidays.
- Oh.

33:15.606 --> 33:18.106
Well, then, is that my Christmas present

33:18.108 --> 33:19.508
in your jacket?

33:22.146 --> 33:23.278
(gasps)

33:23.280 --> 33:26.515
(quietly): Damon

33:31.522 --> 33:36.258
Oh, it's beautiful.

33:38.062 --> 33:40.329
ELENA (whispering): <i>My necklace.</i>

33:46.727 --> 33:48.904
<i>I thought I'd never see it again.</i>

33:48.906 --> 33:50.772
<i>Thank you.</i>

34:09.592 --> 34:11.560
(gasps)

34:42.449 --> 34:44.683
- You seriously couldn't hear that?
- I heard it.

34:44.685 --> 34:46.731
It just sounded like what it is...
a tuning fork.

34:46.755 --> 34:48.920
It gave me a splitting headache.

34:48.922 --> 34:51.257
Ric said it hurt the girls' ears, too.

34:51.259 --> 34:54.260
Maybe it's a signal that
only witches can hear.

34:54.262 --> 34:55.860
Please tell me those siren wretches

34:55.862 --> 34:57.263
aren't also witches.

34:57.265 --> 34:59.465
They sully the name.

34:59.467 --> 35:02.268
My grams used to say that

35:02.270 --> 35:06.305
all witchcraft was rooted
in psychic energy.

35:06.307 --> 35:07.306
Before I knew I had magic,

35:07.308 --> 35:09.008
I believed I was psychic.

35:09.010 --> 35:10.943
Hmm.

35:10.945 --> 35:13.545
And that's what the sirens are.

35:13.547 --> 35:15.514
And Cade.

35:15.516 --> 35:17.608
Oh, gross, we're all connected.

35:17.633 --> 35:19.803
All the more reason to
get the hell out of Dodge.

35:19.834 --> 35:21.954
(on radio): ♪ Noel, noel ♪

35:21.956 --> 35:24.323
Um, you should know

35:24.325 --> 35:27.926
that I bought you T-shirts.

35:27.928 --> 35:32.598
Figured you were tired
of me sleeping in yours.

35:32.600 --> 35:36.168
You're taking me to Paris,
and I bought you T-shirts.

35:36.170 --> 35:38.804
T-shirts!

35:38.806 --> 35:40.739
I suck.

35:40.741 --> 35:45.177
Don't worry about it.

35:45.179 --> 35:47.079
You are the gift I've always wanted.

35:47.081 --> 35:52.017
♪ Of Israel. ♪

35:54.955 --> 35:56.922
(sighs)

36:00.394 --> 36:03.329
Hey. Oh, thank God!

36:03.331 --> 36:05.297
Where's Damon?

36:05.299 --> 36:06.598
He's gone.

36:06.600 --> 36:08.934
Everybody's gone.

36:12.306 --> 36:14.039
Come with me.

36:15.209 --> 36:17.343
Where are we going?

36:17.345 --> 36:18.944
What happened with Cade?

36:18.946 --> 36:20.879
I'll tell you. It's good.

36:20.881 --> 36:23.482
But first...

36:30.424 --> 36:33.692
You could have kissed me anywhere.

36:36.864 --> 36:38.731
I needed at least one
thing I planned for today

36:38.733 --> 36:40.265
to actually work.

36:43.771 --> 36:45.471
I love you.

36:45.473 --> 36:47.840
I love you, too.

36:47.842 --> 36:50.275
Now stop stalling.

36:50.277 --> 36:52.044
(sighs)

36:52.046 --> 36:55.881
We made a deal.

36:55.883 --> 36:59.218
I serve him for a year,
and then I'm done.

36:59.220 --> 37:02.921
Why would you agree to that?

37:04.392 --> 37:06.258
Because what I'm going to do

37:06.260 --> 37:07.593
and how I'm gonna do it

37:07.595 --> 37:10.763
makes it worth it to him.

37:10.765 --> 37:12.798
What are you going to do?

37:16.504 --> 37:18.404
Caroline, please don't, don't...

37:18.406 --> 37:20.239
don't make me say it right now.

37:20.241 --> 37:21.940
Just let me have this moment.

37:23.310 --> 37:25.310
'Cause in seven minutes,
Christmas is over,

37:25.312 --> 37:28.547
and everything changes so...

37:28.549 --> 37:33.152
let me be here, right now...

37:33.154 --> 37:34.620
with you.

37:51.505 --> 37:54.072
(car door opens, shuts)

37:55.676 --> 37:57.843
When you said the Salvatore home,

37:57.845 --> 37:59.445
I thought you meant the front door.

37:59.447 --> 38:01.647
Yeah, we've had enough
guests for one night.

38:01.649 --> 38:05.717
Besides, this is between us.

38:05.719 --> 38:08.554
I'm doing this for them, not you.

38:09.790 --> 38:12.090
- Remember my terms.
- I will.

38:12.092 --> 38:13.055
Girls.

38:13.080 --> 38:14.513
- Seline!
- Seline!

38:20.067 --> 38:23.135
Hey. I missed you guys.

38:23.137 --> 38:26.138
So we are gonna play a little game,

38:26.140 --> 38:29.775
and then you won't remember me,
but that's okay,

38:29.777 --> 38:33.011
'cause you have so many
people that love you.

39:03.611 --> 39:06.311
♪ ♪

39:27.401 --> 39:30.302
BOTH: Thank you, Mommy, thank you, Daddy.

39:30.304 --> 39:32.638
You're very welcome.

39:32.640 --> 39:36.141
We need to get going soon.

39:36.143 --> 39:38.076
(girl gasps)

39:38.078 --> 39:40.579
I know.

39:40.581 --> 39:42.481
I know.

39:42.483 --> 39:44.650
(girls giggling)

39:48.522 --> 39:51.757
♪ ♪

40:03.137 --> 40:04.803
Hop in.

40:04.805 --> 40:06.939
Aren't you light a passenger?

40:06.941 --> 40:08.974
Three's a crowd.

40:26.994 --> 40:29.728
(engine revs, tires screech)

40:35.402 --> 40:37.235
You're gonna want to get under the hood

40:37.237 --> 40:40.005
and flip that humanity switch, Stefan.

40:41.809 --> 40:44.109
Won't be so painful.

40:47.381 --> 40:48.847
Not yet.

40:48.849 --> 40:51.249
Suit yourself, Ebenezer.

40:52.186 --> 40:53.885
(sighs)

40:53.887 --> 40:56.521
The Salvatore brothers,
back on the road again.

40:57.591 --> 40:59.024
We need a theme song or something.

40:59.026 --> 41:00.626
(flips through radio stations)

